Step 3: Add the AI Model File
📋 Instructions
Goal: To copy the large AI model file (model.gguf) from your USB drive into your ai_assistant project folder. The Python code we write will look for this file inside the project directory.

Make sure your USB drive is still plugged in.

We will use the cp (copy) command.

You need to provide the "source" path (where the file is now, on your USB) and the "destination" path (where the file should go, which is your ~/ai_assistant folder).

After copying, we'll use the ls -lh command to list the files in the project folder. This will let you verify that the model.gguf file is there and see its size.

💻 Commands
(Run these in your terminal)

Bash

# 1. Copy the model file from your USB to your project folder
#    (!!! Replace '/media/your_username/MY_USB' with your actual USB path)
cp /media/your_username/MY_USB/model.gguf ~/ai_assistant/

# 2. Verify the file is in your project folder
#    You should see 'model.gguf' listed (around 4.4GB)
ls -lh ~/ai_assistant/
Your ai_assistant folder now contains the venv folder and the model.gguf file. All the necessary components are in place.
